Place: Cafe at the Swedish Church of New York
Review: I had the best cinnamon roll of my life here. It was so good you have to go and they have all these swedish treats!! Highly recommend. The sandwich was just open face bread but the swiss cheese was good

If you’re a rooh fan, baar baar is for you. Personally I don’t think it’s filling enough to justify the cost. Plus you get up and dance and then they put your food out it gets cold, I’m not the biggest fan. I think there are better upscale indian fine dining.
The tacos and diablo sauce were fire. They didnt have AC working which was the only painpoint on a hot summer night but I really liked it. It’s inside Veggie Grill.
I love churros but keeping price and all factors in mind this was okay! worth trying if you want dessert in the area
Decent veg options if you’re in PR.
Phenomenal service! It was so good and I loved the “candy bar” dessert
Go for the lunch deal!! $11 for a 3 course meal!
Crispy Olive & the hot honey pizza + jalapeños 🤌🏾🤌🏾🤌🏾🤌🏾 midwestern style pizza thin crust
Incredible Vegan menu!!!
Awesome place w veg options in PR
The address on taste isnt matching but it was p solid. I think sarvana bhavan is better but the mini idli that were fried in the sauce were superb
Tomato Tart is my new favorite after the blueberry galette
Very good soft serve
I love their green sauce and white sauce and their hot sauce. Falafel is a bit crispy/on the harder size but still a really great cheap meal in nyc
Easy slice - got the Sicilian! P standard but good
Solid Food @ Mackinack island. I loved their chickpea burger and margarita flatbread
I loved the rivieria salad and the zucchini and squash pizza! And lovely outdoor seating >>
Really good ice cream!
Not a bad wait and the soufflé pancakes wedw ao cool

VEGAN Italian but you can’t even tell. The drinks were amazing, my fav was the nuts and berry because it felt like a smoothie w alch and the tiramasu was also fab esp when you’re with someone who doesnt eat eggs in dessert
I love their pastries. It reminds me of fox in the snow and how good those are back in Columbus
The chutney tasted like the bottle kind, wasnt a fan
The silcian was so light and fluffy + they got hot honey
Get the Gose, tastes like Mango Juice. Best beer.

$95 for 2 so split that in half and that’s your bill. It included a whole bottle of wine, massive fondue plate, a large fig salad, and a tasting plate with hummus, pita, pickles, (meat), stuffed peppers, spinakopita, and grape leaves. It was an insane amount of food for new york city, would love to go again and see if it can be split between 4 people rather than 2. AND it included dessert.
Service was slow and wasn’t a fan of the kale of gorgonzola items
This place is cash only which was annoying because we didn’t know before hand but overall solid meal.
Super fun place to just dance and have a drink at. And they have a disco ball
Converted school into a restaurant, the espresso coke and lime was interesting but all the coffees were so good
Very cute speak easy and very vibey / chinatown esq. Drinks were also very good. Id come back here for sure
Swedish Candy Store! They had all the nostalgia candies + gelatin free options
The backbean frita was so good and the coconut batido!!!
I thought it was decent pizza but not sure if it was worth getting there super super early and coming back 4 hours later. The crust was good but it you go def get the calzone
I love this bakery. Amazing desserts perfect for birthdays. The line is long but usually very efficient.
I wasnt amazed but not a bad option and pretty cheap. If you’re in the area it’s worth trying.
We walked in and they started playing Bollywood music. Better than SOBs for sureeee
Cheap meal and despite the name you wouldn’t expect the asian entrees to be good but the general tso’s was incredible. Also the vegan sushi!! I would def go back their sandwiches were also v good
Excellent Arepas. They werent oily at all. Loved the coffee and the vibes it was too cute
So many veggie options and its so buttery rather than salty. Best kind of ramen and fab desserts
Excellent drinks and very fun event space/venue
Cheapest High Tea in NYC hands down
The pretzel had this artichoke dip and I loved it

At first I thought this was just a breaking experience BUT you can order drinks and then go in a room and smash your glasses as well. And if you just want stuff to break there’s a 5 for $20 deal and they give you glasses and mugs to throw. Would 100% go back such a cool fun bar concept.
The food the first time i went was incredible, this time it was alright. Worth going to in jackson heights area

All vegan, loved the animal fries but next time rather than getting the mushroom i wish i tried the original. The staff was also very kind and they let us sample all the fancy colas. Would also go back for the dessert
Better than Kati Roll co. Fun cheap meal def a go to when I’m in the neighborhood
Low Fat Olive Cream Cheese

Okay the wait was long (anytime ive tried to go before it’s been longer) but the food and drinks were incredible. I felt like time stopped while being inside this place and I had fantastic company while waiting in line so that made it go by fast :)
Pad Thai w Vegan chicken but the burger was my favorite
Best Burrito (califonia style) in Manhattan
Cute drinks spot
